Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery vessel, the fabric is grey in section, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and remains of eight lines of black-painted demotic text.
Curator's comments: Being studied for publication by Bryan Kraemer. Cemeteries and Osireion Excavations Group
Bibliographic references: Frankfort 1933 / The Cenotaph of Seti I at Abydos (no.19?)
